spanGrp.span: I will start the nzürna story for you
they were staying there in yabär
dim (AN) = nzrm (KO) = sour; this could be "dimés" which means "sour" in Anta
they set off to poison the creek
there was one man with two wifes
the child was not big, a girl, about this size
the child followed later, the girl
fi nzür.na ŋa.re fo.ba wa.tay.ʔa fəz ma.sun zə.ba ma.ne rä ka.far
but the nzürna was there in the wataya forest in masu. a big forest
she was coming from there with the net
wa.ti ʔe.moth fäth zə.ba ka.tan zrä.ro
that is were they saw each other
that was what the small girl thought
she told her "you go over there!"
"from there you chase (the fish) this way"
ta.ba nzür.na ŋa.ref yak.me ʔa.ne thwa.na.thə.rəm kwaf.yu.nzə.rəm mə.thi
when it was full. the nzürna was eating them quickly. she swallowed the whole fish
kanzkanz = crooked; mean a point in the creek here
we ʔän.mə.ri.nza we gwə.rər gwə.rər gwə.rər
gwrr kwan = sound of swallowing something down
again she chased them, and swallowed them
naf ʔe.moth fä.thəf zre.mar ŋa.me za.ne ke.ke rä
the little girl saw her thinking "this is not a mother
ni.ma zwa.mä.gwə.rə.mo fəz za.we ka.far fəz.fo wa.tay.ʔa.fo
she (nzürna) is leading her away to the forest, to the big forest, to wataya
she said "you go over there. a bit away"
ʔe.moth fə.thə ma.ne wə.ya.ka ʔa.ne bo.bo
the girl went over there, to there
bad fä fof gwar.gwar zath.kä.fa tha.ri.si
she started digging the mud over there
metathesis: gabrin (some people say "garbin"); property noun: no gabrinthé rä `the water is milky dirty'
only the dirty water was flowing
wa.tik ʔe.moth fäth ma.ne re.ra ŋa.kwi.ra moth
the girl was running to the road
she got to the road, she still she ran
in the afternoon (she arrived) at her father's
the nzürna is chasing me. I was just netting with the nzürna
like this like this like this
with other ladies, therefore plural even though two mothers
not quite clear what he means
nä ŋa.re zrä.ko.thəm ko.fä ya.re.gwər na.bi zan na.bi zan wəf.nza
he chased the other wife. (who was) still loaded with fish. with the bow he beat her
we nä zrä.ko.thəm na.bi zan na.bi zan wəf.nzər
he chased the other wife. he belted her with the bow
ʔe.moth fäth ʔa.ne fof ʔe.foth bä səf.rä.rəm zi.zi
the little girl... the sun was there.. it was afternoon
wa.tik ni.ma si.ze.nzo ʔe.moth fäth thrath.bəth wa.wa mə.nzen
then, they put two girls of the same age in the yam house
at the back of the house
thä.bu.me thä.bu ʔe.rak.nath wa.tik ʔer.dik.nath wa.tik ni.ma
raksi = braiding, crawling; rdiknsi = tie together
they twisted their hair, they tied them together
them covered them with the mat and put yams on top
the nzürna already came and leaned against the banana
from there, she was watching them
dd wth = is the soil thrown up the by worms digging in the ground
she started thorwing soil at them
she was making the people sleepy
she went inside and saw them
she told the other one "no this one, this one"
she untied them from the hair
she carried this one to the door
bök kwan = schmatzendes geräusch; kann benutzt werden, wenn ein pfeil durch ein tier geht, oder tier sex haben (als witz)
she pulled out one of her eyes
sriszi = send; she sends her hands (in plural)
the buttocks she pushed her hand in her ass
the girl's intestines; the prefixes indexes 3SG:IO
talking to me or somebody there
ka.be ʔet.fəth zäb.thath wä.na.tha wa.tik fa.ren
people slept. she ate her. she finished her up. okay, on the tree
you tell (him). why are you looking around?
she hung the (rest of the) intestines
only the head, she carried to wataya
wa.tik fä fof ŋa.so.ga war.fo na.fa.ne.mä.wä mə.nzen
she climbed up on top to her own house
na.fa.fi.səf za.ma.ra oh bä za.ne ke.re.re zə nə.ŋan.fi.yo.kwər
her husband saw her: "oh, you have just made this problem!"
"you have already eaten a human being!"
tauri kufak = place name in the north of rouku
they slept and woke up like this (shocked) "nothing"
they only saw the intestines on the post
za.mi.ya.rath mü.sa oh zä zəf wə.thə.kə.gər
miyasi = pick up; müsa = the small thing that is used for tracking; müsamüsa = restless movement (like a pig or dog searching for something)
they went for her. (followed) her trace/smell. "she is inside here"
kwathkwath = hope for, plan for (property noun)
with their magic (plans), the wrapped the watchmacallit
they piled firewood at the base
it burned and burned and burned
she was about to look outside "oh fire"
she tried to put it off by peeing, but no
she tried to spray out the fire with her shit
she threw it. to extinguish the fire. but no
rzifthaksi = push over; the tree fell here
finished with the tree and all. the tree fell
si kukakuka rä = bird; the bird is always around when the fire is burning; wännor
the kukakuka bird was trying to sing
thngthng = charcoal; she was trying to get into the bird, but the sorcerers prevented that by grinding up her charcoal remains
they grabbed the bird. they grinded the charcoal remains (of her)
zo.kwa.si fof zä.bəth nzür.na tri.ka.si ni.ma.me fof rä
the story is finished. that is how the nzürna trikasi goes
ke.ke nzür.na tri.ka.si rä ka.be tri.ka.si rä za.ne
it is not a nzürna story, but a story from a man
"into" is expressed by the purposive case: zokwasi nzürna trikasiR wkwthenzath
they turned it into a nzürna story
ka.be zo.kwa.si ʔa.ha nzür.na tri.ka.si za.rath
a people story... the made it a nzürna story
bres mon.wä bres mon.wä zə.ba ya.na.tha
za.ne ka.far ya.ra ʔa.ne ka.tan re.ra ʔe.moth fäth
this one was big (bres), but she was small
wa.tay.ʔa zə.ba ma.ne rä ma.su za.we fo.ba fof ren.ra ʔa.ne nzür.na ŋa.re
wataya is here. she came from the masu side that nzürna
refers to the time that I went with the boy to this place to collect mtök leaves
really where you were getting the mtök leaves with them.
rou.ku ka.be ya.ra na.fa.ne nə.ge wä.na.thra
the man from rouku, she ate his child
no name, the oldman did not mention the name to me
the yabär creek that lies there
bo.ba ni mo.ba nam.nzər bi mo.bo ʔe.ko.gər ya.bär ʔa.ne fof
there where we are staying. where the sagos are standing, that is yabär
where are our sago are standing
moth fä fof zə.fəth.nəm ni.ma tət.fö.fo dim.sa.thak.fo
that is were the road went to dimsathak
at the big creek there were walking
that is where nzürna ŋare saw her
